******
[4] Cholera - China
Date: Sun 9 Jun 2013
Source: SINA, Xinhua News Agency report [edited]
http://english.sina.com/china/2013/0609/597813.html


A total of 1526 people died of infectious diseases in the Chinese mainland in May 2013 and AIDS was the most deadly, revealed the National Health and Family Planning Commission on Sun 9 Jun 2013.

A total of 721 605 infectious disease cases were reported in the Chinese mainland in May 2013, the statement said. Among them, 8 cases of cholera were reported but none of them resulted in death. Plague and cholera are categorized as class A infectious diseases, the most serious bracket.

--
